        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 24 at 2:57PM CDT until July 24 at 3:30PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>SVRLOT

The National Weather Service in Chicago has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northeastern Kendall County in northeastern Illinois...
Northwestern Will County in northeastern Illinois...

* Until 330 PM CDT.

* At 257 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Romeoville to near Shorewood, moving east at 30
mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Severe thunderstorms will be near...
Woodridge, Bolingbrook, Romeoville, Joliet, Lockport, Homer Glen,
and Crest Hill around 305 PM CDT.
New Lenox and Ingalls Park around 310 PM CDT.

Other locations impacted by these severe thunderstorms include
Fairmont, Crystal Lawns, Rockdale, and Preston Heights.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
